	<Title>
		Recipe: Chocolate pudding pies
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Chocolate pudding pies &amp;mdash; one of many healthy recipes from Mayo Clinic.
	</Abstract>
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		6
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; These quick-and-easy chocolate pudding pies make great desserts or snacks. Instead of using sprinkles for garnish, you can top the pies with diced fresh fruit, such as strawberries or raspberries.&lt;/p&gt;
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;In a medium-sized bowl, add the pudding and milk. Whisk until evenly mixed. Cover and refrigerate until the pudding thickens, about 5 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Spoon 1/3 cup prepared pudding into each graham cracker crust. Top each with 1 tablespoon whipped topping and garnish with sprinkles. Serve immediately.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;p&gt;1 package (3 ounces) instant chocolate pudding&lt;br /&gt;
2 cups fat-free milk&lt;br /&gt;
6 graham cracker crusts, individual sizes&lt;br /&gt;
6 tablespoons whipped topping&lt;br /&gt;
Sprinkles, for garnish&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Ingredients>
